              <title>Helen Crump: Design Project:: Digital Me -Understanding Digital Literacies</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7057</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7057</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>My situation </strong></p>
<p>I&rsquo;m an adult literacy tutor and I live on the West Coast of Ireland (originally from Nottingham) . I'm also a very recent graduate of St. Angela's College, Sligo where I completed an M.A. awarded by NUI Galway in Technology, Learning, Innovation and Change.<br /> <br /> I&rsquo;m interested in digital literacies and social learning, which ideally I'd like to teach online in a Higher Education or professional development context. For that reason, I'm developing my skills and knowledge in relation to online pedagogy and instructional design (which I&rsquo;m going to refer to as learning design from now on).<br /> <br /> <strong>My learning design project</strong><br /> <br /> I&rsquo;m already developing my course through participation in <a href="http://pedagogyfirst.org/wppf12/">Pedagogy First </a>&nbsp;,which is a small MOOC like programme led by volunteers of Mira Costa College, San Diego, which focuses on online pedagogical skills. <br /> <br /> However, within OLDSMOOC I&rsquo;d like to develop some learning design skills so as to help me develop my course as effectively as possible. <br /> <br /> I have been blogging about my progress on the course so far: <a href="http://learningcreep.wordpress.com/">http://learningcreep.wordpress.com/</a></p>]]></description>
